  "target_response": {
    "text": "Trust both — they measure different things, and today they're compatible. Your recovery score is 79% because the overnight systemic signals were good: your HRV of 60 ms is a touch above its 30-day baseline of 58 ms. But the score has no direct read on local muscle damage, and your logged soreness of 4 out of 5 is exactly that. So the decision: train, but route around the quads — a moderate upper-body or easy spin day uses the systemic capacity the 79% reflects without loading tissue that's still repairing. Concretely, I'd move squats to later in the week and reassess once soreness drops a couple of points. Driving heavy knee-dominant work through 4-out-of-5 soreness mostly buys worse movement quality, not extra adaptation.",
